cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper introduces a novel approach to statistical relational learning that involves kernel-based learning on expressive logical and relational representations. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of logic programming and deductive databases, which suggests it could also belong to the sub-categories of natural language processing (cs.CL) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
